abstract: CARBONDALE, Penn., Jan. 23.--Twenty inches of snow has fallen since Friday morning, blocking the railroads and highways leading from this city. The railroad companies have been compelled to abandon their trains on account of the storm. Telegraph and telephone lines are down in many places, cutting off communication with points east and west. Trains were detained over night, for the first time in years, in consequence of the storm.
